    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Diagnostic Software Operation - Reset Service Interval Lamp - Using
        Cruise Switches (CF)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010304.2" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Using Cruise Switches (CF)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para id="s305010304.2.1">Read and be familiar with all steps and time limits in this procedure before
                    starting.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Steps 2 and 3 must be completed with three seconds of ignition switch on.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn ignition switch to ON. (Do not crank the engine.)</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f305010350" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj31/J31162.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cruise switches (CF)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and release the top of CRUISE RPM and RESUME+ switches simultaneously.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The top of CRUISE RPM switch is not labeled. Pressing the top of CRUISE RPM will latch the
                        switch and illuminate a small red light at the top, indicating that cruise is on.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and release RESUME+ switch three more times.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and hold RESUME+ switch for three seconds.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the RESUME+ switch and press the bottom of CRUISE RPM switch to unlatch. Service
                Interval Lamp is reset.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
